{"plot_notes":"Swan Point Cemetery, Providence RI. FindAGrave Memorial #156013083."},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":11,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":2,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"I01252","mother_id":"HD4971"},"number_of_marriages":0,"marriages":[],"education":[{"school_name":"Hope High School","type":"secondary","notes":"Hope High School, Providence."},{"school_name":"Brown University","dates":"Class of 1945","type":"undergraduate","notes":"Brown University class of 1945; college years interrupted by Army Air Corps service WWII."}],"career":[{"role":"Owner","organization":"Braided Rug and Specialties Co. (Pawtucket RI)","notes":"Owner of the former Braided Rug and Specialties Co. in Pawtucket; worked with his father for many years."}],"military_service":[{"branch":"United States Army Air Corps","war":"World War II","notes":"Served in the Meteorology Division of the Army Air Corps during World War II; service interrupted Brown University degree."}],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[{"name_element":"Wesley William","inspired_by_id":"I01252","description":"Named for his father Wesley William Yando."}],"artworks":[],"tags":["wwii","extraordinary_longevity"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[{"type":"military","related_id":"I01249","display_label":"B-17G radio operator, 95th Bomb Group, 34 combat missions","link_text":"Ethan Allen Hitchcock Shepley Jr.","notes":"Two WWII Army Air Corps men in the same Butler-Bragdon family circle. Wesley Yando Jr. served in the Army Air Corps Meteorology Division — interrupting his Brown University degree — while his first cousin Margaret 'Peggy' Bragdon Shepley's second husband Ethan Shepley Jr. flew thirty-four combat missions over Germany as a B-17G radio operator with the 95th Bomb Group (Heavy), 8th AAF, based at Horham, Suffolk. Meteorology kept the bombers flying; Shepley's bomber crews depended on weather forecasts like the ones Yando trained for."}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"military","header":"Brown 1945 — interrupted by Army Air Corps Meteorology","body":"Born February 10, 1924 in Pawtucket, his Brown University degree was interrupted by service in the Army Air Corps Meteorology Division during World War II. He finished as Brown class of 1945, then worked alongside his father for many years at Braided Rug and Specialties Co. of Pawtucket. He died at Pawtucket on December 10, 2015 aged ninety-one."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"wesley-yando-jr-1924"},"HD4972":{"id":"HD4972","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Edwin","middle_name":"Stewart","last_name":"Butler","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"Edwin Stewart Butler"},"gender":"male","birth":{"year":1902,"month":10,"day":11,"state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1984,"month":11,"day":10,"county":"Pinellas","state":"Florida","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"plot_notes":"FindAGrave Memorial #283339504."},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":10,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":2,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"HD4968","mother_id":"I01245"},"number_of_marriages":0,"marriages":[],"education":[],"career":[{"role":"Production Clerk","organization":"RBW (New York)","notes":"Retired production clerk for RBW in New York."}],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiratio